+# Release v0.7.0 ‚Äî v3 Upgrade: Data Layer, Real Gemini Categorization & Fiscal Periods
+
+**Date:** 2026-05-29
+**Bump:** MINOR (`0.6.0 ‚Üí 0.7.0`)
+**Tag:** `v0.7.0` ‚Üí release commit
+
+## Why this version
+
+Backward-compatible feature release, **no breaking changes** since `0.6.0`.
+Under `0.x` semantic versioning a feature release increments the **minor**, so
+this lands as `0.7.0`. The bump is derived from the merged history, not guessed:
+`git log v0.6.0..HEAD` is two `feat` commits ‚Äî `0ace17d` (v3 upgrade) and
+`44191ce` (fiscal-period utility) ‚Äî both additive, neither breaking.
+
+## Headline
+
+The app gains its **first server API route** and a **swappable data boundary**:
+`POST /api/categorize` runs real Gemini-backed transaction categorization (with
+a deterministic heuristic fallback so keyless builds still work), the dashboard
+reads through a single typed data layer that can be repointed at a real DB
+without touching consumers, and the ledger picks up a pure `getFiscalPeriod`
+utility for reporting and transaction grouping.
+
+## What's new
+
+- **Real Gemini transaction categorization** ‚Äî `POST /api/categorize` (Node
+  runtime). Given `{ description, amount }` returns typed JSON
+  `{ debitAccount, creditAccount, category, confidence, rationale, source }`.
+  Calls `gemini-3.5-flash` when `GEMINI_API_KEY` is set; otherwise (and on any
+  parse/network failure) falls back to a deterministic keyword‚Üíaccount
+  heuristic. Wired into the landing page via a new `CategorizePanel`.
+- **Swappable data-layer boundary** (`src/lib/data/`) ‚Äî typed async fetchers
+  (`getTransactions`, `getCustomers`, `getLedgerStats`, ‚Ä¶) plus pure aggregation
+  helpers behind one boundary; dashboard pages now fetch as async server
+  components. Bodies return mock fixtures today, repointable at a real DB/API.
+- **Ledger explorer UI** ‚Äî client-side search, income/expense filtering,
+  sortable Date/Amount/Confidence columns, CSV export, and empty-state handling;
+  view preferences persist to localStorage via a Zustand `persist` store.
+- **Fiscal-period date utility** ‚Äî `getFiscalPeriod` maps a `Date` to its fiscal
+  period (year/quarter/month + bounds); pure, fail-loud `RangeError`,
+  `fiscalYearStartMonth` validated `1..12` [ADR-0006].
+- Dashboard route segment gains `loading.tsx` skeletons and an `error.tsx` retry
+  boundary now that its components fetch async.
+
+## Quality gate
+
+All four gates green on the release commit:
+
+- `tsc --noEmit` ‚Äî clean
+- `eslint .` ‚Äî clean
+- `tsx --test` ‚Äî **87/87 pass**
+- `next build` ‚Äî success (8 routes; `/api/categorize` server-rendered on demand)
+
+## Known issues / carry-forward
+
+- **postcss XSS ‚Äî GHSA-qx2v-qp2m-jg93** (moderate) remains open: `next@16.2.6`
+  nests `postcss@8.4.31` (< 8.5.10). Non-blocking (build-time CSS stringify, not
+  user-input-fed). Fix = a one-line `package.json` `overrides` pin
+  (`"postcss": ">=8.5.10"`); do **not** `npm audit fix --force` (it proposes a
+  wrong `next@9.3.3` downgrade).
+- **Security findings on the new `/api/categorize` route** (filed by the
+  security scan at this commit, routed to engineering): unauthenticated /
+  unthrottled paid-model endpoint (cost-DoS) and raw user `description`
+  interpolated into the model prompt (prompt injection). Bounded today by
+  shape-validation + heuristic fallback + React JSX escaping; recommended
+  hardening = auth + rate-limit + a chart-of-accounts allow-list on returned
+  accounts. Does not block this release but should be addressed before the route
+  is exposed to untrusted traffic.
